It is important to mention that the measured PL spectrum may not reflect the aforementioned band-to-band recombination processes of electrons and holes, but it may demonstrate emission associated with other processes. One of the most well-known process is the formation of a free exciton, i.e., electrostatically bound electron–hole (e–h) pairs. Due to their binding energy, the emission energy of excitons (EPLX\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
